This paper deals with the problem of forming robust clusters in cognitive radio networks, which involves aspects of networking (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), and game theory (cs.GT). The paper proposes both centralized and distributed solutions, which involve algorithms and optimization (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also discusses the dynamics of ad hoc cognitive radio networks, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI, followed by cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.AI, and cs.DC.
